1_Q20: Using zoom, using polls, and the speakers were excellent at providing detail around the subject matter.
1_Q35: The second poll didn't work for me. I was able to put my response in the chat.

1_Q20: The speakers very well articulated the seemingly complex nature of trust in community and research partnerships in understandable and relatable terms. The presentation content was shared by speakers in a way that strengthened the overall key learning for participants.
Loved the two-sides questions asked via polleverywhere; seeing the different words used for researches and community members was striking.
1_Q35: Possibly provide list of community organizations doing different kinds of work throughout region and state.

Q2_6_TEXT: research staff at a different university

6_Q35: I would reconsider the wording of the question for the second breakout group. It was really broad for people who are very new to equitable partnerships

6_Q20: The speakers were very knowlegable and experienced.

1_Q20: Reverend Bailliard's presentation was very thought provoking and engaging. The asset small group exercise was helpful.

4_Q20: Everything. And the small one-on-one breakout was very productive for us.
I really appreciated the breakout session!

6_Q35: More about community asset map and suggestions for other avenues to reach community

4_Q35: consider having a mock data party as part of presentation

Q2_6_TEXT: research staff at a different university
3_Q20: The activity and discussion about the activity really facilitated my learning and had me questioning budgets I have made for current projects and considering how they might have been more equitable
I enjoyed the budgeting process although it took me a minute to wrap my head around it. In the end, it fostered great conversations.

5_Q20: The discussion was great! Loved the use of Miro. Wish we had more time to discuss everything!
5_Q35: I know its hard when the group isn't interactive but more time for discussion at the very end would be great!

4_Q20: The breakout session activity was good way to help reinforce the learning
4_Q35: Perhaps share examples of the concepts or presentation before the session (1-2 days before the session), consider a preactivity for this session.
5_Q20: The breakout session activity is good way to reinforce the teaching
